      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification is satisfied by benchmark problems documented in the Ansys Mechanical verification manual (ANSYS VM series) covering linear elastic beam bending and contact mechanics. Level 2 requires at least one benchmark comparison relevant to the physics of interest.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical verification manual benchmarks (VM1, VM6, VM32) confirm correct implementation of linear elastic solid mechanics and frictionless contact. Results match analytical solutions within 0.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A mesh convergence study on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface must demonstrate that the QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) change by less than 2% between the production mesh and a uniformly refined mesh. Level 3 is required given the stress concentration sensitivity at the screw-rod junction.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed with three mesh densities (coarse ~120k elements, medium ~340k elements, fine ~910k elements). QoI variation between medium and fine meshes was 1.4% for stiffness, 1.1% for yield force, and 0.9% for force at 40 mm. Production mesh is the medium density."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Default Ansys iterative solver settings used; residual convergence criterion set to 1e-6. No solver divergence or poor conditioning warnings observed across all 11 construct simulations. Numerical solver error is considered controlled at Level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Standard operating procedures for model setup and boundary condition application are documented. A second analyst independently reviewed all model inputs and boundary conditions prior to simulation execution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form adequacy is demonstrated when the normalized validation metric E/uval is below 1.96 for all three QoIs across the N=11 ensemble, where uval combines experimental measurement uncertainty and model prediction uncertainty. Level 3 is required because model form errors in contact representation could materially affect yield force predictions.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model with titanium alloy properties (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, yield=880 MPa) used throughout. Geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime. Contact between screw and rod modeled as frictionless surface-to-surface. E/uval computed as 0.87, 1.12, and 1.44 for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm respectively — all below 1.96 threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions must be sourced from traceable measurements on the actual test specimens or certified material certificates. Level 3 requires documented uncertainty bounds on all primary model inputs.",
      "rationale": "Material certificates for Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw stock provided by DePuy Synthes. Geometric dimensions measured via CMM on three representative screws; mean values used in model with ±1 standard deviation documented. Young's modulus uncertainty ±3 GPa propagated through sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test sample population must be N≥10 constructs from at least two independent lots, tested across at least two laboratories, with documented traceability of sample identity. Level 3 is required to support statistical comparison of FEA predictions against experimental variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested. Samples drawn from two production lots. Testing conducted at two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes R&D). Full sample traceability documented."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol followed at both laboratories. A single loading rate (5 mm/min) and single offset distance (25 mm) were used across all tests. The required level of 3 is not fully achieved because only one test condition (single load configuration) was evaluated; multiple offset distances or loading rates would be needed to fully characterize model fidelity across the test condition space. This shortfall is noted but accepted given the scope of the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Model boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry: rigid block constraints at proximal and distal ends, 25 mm offset, axial compressive load applied through the superior block. Equivalency confirmed by overlay of fixture CAD with model boundary condition schematic."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison must use both a percentage difference criterion (<10% mean QoI difference) and a normalized validation metric (E/uval < 1.96). Both criteria must be satisfied for all three QoIs. Level 3 is required because the COU decision consequence is Medium and model influence is Medium.",
      "rationale": "Mean percentage differences: stiffness 4.2%, yield force 6.8%, force at 40 mm 5.1% — all below 10% threshold. E/uval values: 0.87, 1.12, 1.44 — all below 1.96. Both acceptance criteria satisfied for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the quantities used in the regulatory submission to characterize construct mechanical performance. QoI relevance is considered adequate."
    },
    {
